This paper is about the impact of GPU Dynamic Voltage and Frequency Scaling (DVFS) on the energy consumption and performance of deep learning. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the following sub-categories:

- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): This sub-category covers research on computer hardware architecture, which includes GPUs.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category covers research on machine learning, which includes deep neural networks.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): This sub-category covers research on neural networks and related algorithms, which includes deep learning.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): This sub-category covers research on systems and control, which includes energy-efficient computing.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): This sub-category covers research on distributed and parallel computing, which includes GPU computing.
